This is a feature request submitted on behalf of a JIRA Administrator:

To better conceptualize what internal work is done for what external customer my company has a custom select field called Customer.  Additionally, in the process of building out a Service Desk implementation we built a project for tracking customer details with a separate issue for each customer we work with.  Issues in this project are generated from accounts in SalesForce and then a matching service desk organization and Customer select value need to be created.  Currently this entire workflow can be managed using webhooks and APIs except for the part of updating or creating values for the customer select field.

This is creating a bottle neck in our process for rolling out new customers that requires a JIRA admin to handle, and has the potential to break numerous automations we have built.  Seeing that you have already developed API endpoints for managing this type of field when it is created by an Connect Add-on it seems only sensible to offer it for custom select field types generated by the native UI.

